entries.title: Around 500 migrants crossed Channel to UK today
entries.description: Around 500 people crossed from France to England across the Channel today, according to Sky sources.

entries.title: Treasury reviewing processes after 'helping Russian mercenary group boss circumvent sanctions to sue British journalist'
entries.description: The Treasury is reviewing its processes after reports it helped the head of Russia's notorious mercenary Wagner Group circumvent UK sanctions to take a British journalist to court.

entries.title: At least one dead and several injured in Spanish church 'terror attack' stabbing
entries.description: At least one person has been killed and several others injured in an attack carried out by someone with a bladed weapon at a church in southern Spain.

entries.title: Two dead after man stabs passengers on train in Germany
entries.description: Two people have been killed in a knife attack on a train in Germany, according to media reports.

entries.title: 'That's a very good idea': Russian mercenary boss appears to laugh off claims of plot to assassinate him
entries.description: Russian mercenary group leader has Yevgeny Prigozhin appeared to laugh off claims of a plot to assassinate him, describing it as "a very good idea".

entries.title: Zelenskyy 'thankful' for extra tanks as Kremlin says they 'will burn'
entries.description: The Ukrainian president has told Sky News he is "very happy" and "thankful" that Germany has decided to supply 14 Leopard 2 tanks - but warned the quantity and delivery time of the vehicles is "critical".

entries.title: Police and students clash in India as tensions rise over banned BBC Modi documentary
entries.description: Tensions have escalated in India as police and students were involved in scuffles over a BBC documentary examining Prime Minister Narendra Modi's role during the 2002 Gujarat riots.

entries.title: Dismissed teacher stands outside school for second day amid trans row
entries.description: An Irish teacher dismissed because of a transgender pronouns row returned to the premises a day after being arrested for trespassing at the school.

entries.title: Five die and thousands swarm airport as snow and ice cause chaos in east Asia
entries.description: Thousands of travellers have swarmed an airport in South Korea trying to leave a holiday island after hundreds of flights were cancelled by cold weather gripping east Asia.

entries.title: Handcuffed Andrew Tate hits out in Romania, saying 'there is no justice'
entries.description: Self-proclaimed misogynist influencer Andrew Tate has said "there is no justice in Romania" as he was escorted in handcuffs from a police van.

entries.title: Man dies after being shot by dog
entries.description: A man has died after a dog stepped on a rifle and shot him from the rear of a truck in the US state of Kansas.

entries.title: Blow to Putin as both Germany and US confirm they will send tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Germany will supply Ukraine with 14 Leopard 2 tanks and has given allies permission to send theirs too – despite threats from Russia – while the US has confirmed it will send over 31 M1 Abrams tanks and provide training to the country's troops.

entries.title: Ants can 'sniff out' cancer in urine, scientists find
entries.description: Ants can smell cancer in urine, scientists have found.

entries.title: Kanye West could be denied entry to Australia over antisemitic comments
entries.description: Kanye West cold be denied entry to Australia over his history of antisemitic remarks, according to a government minister.

entries.title: Does Germany sending tanks to Ukraine mean the US is open to sending their own?
entries.description: Generously, you'd call the tank debate an evolution of views among Western policymakers.
